1
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:00,440
<i>It's almost every woman's dream,</i>

2
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:04,840
<i>whether from the age of ten, 20, or 30.</i>

3
00:02:04,920 --> 00:02:07,000
<i>Us women have dreamed</i>

4
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:09,840
<i>of marrying a decent man one day.</i>

5
00:02:09,919 --> 00:02:13,360
<i>I have that dream too,</i>
<i>even on my 30th birthday,</i>

6
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,440
<i>when I'm almost too old for such a dream.</i>

7
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,280
Our groom's ready!

8
00:02:22,760 --> 00:02:24,720
Why's our model a blond?

9
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,840
Aren't we going
for "Sweet Honeymoon Tour in Asia"?

10
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:30,760
So how come the groom's a white guy, huh?

11
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,800
Uh… Well…

12
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:35,600
We're on a tight budget,
so we had to hire a different model.

13
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:38,840
But Ms. Whan, isn't it more expensive
to hire a white model?

14
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,680
I just so happened to find Robert
on Khaosan Road last night,

15
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:46,200
so I asked him to model for us.

16
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:49,280
He didn't ask for much at all, though.

17
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,880
Just one Pad Thai and we're good.

18
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:54,320
So you asked me to model

19
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:56,360
'cause of the tight budget too, right?

20
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:06,320
Did anyone tell our clients
about the offer yet?

21
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:09,520
No. We wanted to wait
until the documents were ready.

22
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:16,040
Whan, can you edit the details?

23
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:17,400
Don't say it's in Asia.

24
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:20,680
I'll replan the whole tour
and add Europe as a destination.

25
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:22,120
I'll send it to you when I'm done.

26
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:23,920
Sure.

27
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:27,440
There's our legendary manager.

28
00:03:27,520 --> 00:03:29,120
You really can manage it all, Mook.

29
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:31,600
Good work!

30
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,840
Can we hurry?

31
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,120
I have another shoot after this.

32
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:37,280
Got it.

33
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,280
Good.

34
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:47,840
Okay.

35
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,360
- Okay, all done.
- Looks great.

36
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:50,280
Thank you, guys.

37
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,320
- Thank you!
- Thank you.

38
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,240
Thank you.

39
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:53,560
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

40
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:54,480
Thank you.

41
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,880
Could you help me?

42
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,200
Mook!

43
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,800
Send them to our usual press,
and don't forget--

44
00:04:14,880 --> 00:04:16,079
- Ask for a discount and credits.
- Discount and credits.

45
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:17,480
Nice!

46
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,800
MR. PAT

47
00:04:24,880 --> 00:04:26,800
- Shoot, shoot, shoot!
- Shoot who?

48
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:29,800
Yes?

49
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:31,600
Yeah, I'm starting the car.

50
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:34,640
Yes, I'll meet you at the school.

51
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,840
Alright, see you!

52
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,960
Bye, guys!

53
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,440
Where are you going, Mook?

54
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:39,560
- What about tonight?
- I'll let you know!

55
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,320
Don't forget the angel costume, Mook!

56
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,760
Her? As an angel?

57
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:48,720
Are you sure? She's clearly the devil.

58
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:52,240
It's not her costume. It's Kongkwan's.

59
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:54,640
It's good that you're here, Tit.
Come help us pack up.

60
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:56,160
Come on. I just got here!

61
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,440
Can't I sit down first?

62
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:58,680
You helping or not?

63
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,760
Of course I am.

64
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:03,560
I'd do anything for you, May.

65
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:07,360
- Come here.
- We're doing it now?

66
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:11,960
ACADEMIC EXCELLENCE AND VIRTUE

67
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:29,520
Just wait a little longer, Kongkwan.

68
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,040
Our parents are coming.

69
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,000
Mommy's late for sure.

70
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:36,120
She's always this way.

71
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:06,040
Excuse me. Sorry!

72
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:11,000
- Mook!
- Mr. Pat!

73
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,680
Uh, I'm sorry!

74
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,200
- Uh…
- Hold on, Mook.

75
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,440
- Just a sec.
- Sure.

76
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:30,320
You okay?

77
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,480
- I have to go. My daughter's waiting.
- Wait, Mook.

78
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,120
Okay.

79
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,280
Mommy!

80
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:51,200
Poonpun, come on.

81
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,360
I'll see you then.

82
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,680
Hi.

83
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,320
Kongkwan…

84
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,640
Hey.

85
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,120
Angels don't cry, honey.

86
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:07,560
Here.

87
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,680
Wanna see what mommy brought?

88
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,160
Ta-da!

89
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:17,920
It's your costume. Isn't it pretty?

90
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,440
Let me turn you into an angel, okay?

91
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:45,600
You're so cute, honey!

92
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:59,320
I've got the costume and the wand…

93
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,120
Where are the wings?

94
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,120
Did I forget them?!

95
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:09,840
They're here, Mommy.

96
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:12,640
Oh, how silly of me.

97
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:15,360
Come on. Let's become an angel now.

98
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:16,920
Let's go!

99
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:22,760
Ooh, the apples look yummy.

100
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:25,160
I know! Shall we eat them?

101
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:28,600
Eat one and you'll grow smarter!

102
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:31,480
Don't eat it! You'll die!

103
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:35,760
- Don't eat it! Don't!
- Don't!

104
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,240
Our kids sure are cute.

105
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,559
Eat it! Eat it!

106
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:39,919
Don't!

107
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,600
- Eat it!
- Don't!

108
00:08:42,679 --> 00:08:45,600
- Eat it!
- Don't eat it!

109
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:46,800
- Eat it!
- Don't eat it!

110
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:48,200
- Eat it!
- Don't eat it!

111
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:50,440
- Eat it!
- Don't!

112
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:58,600
- Mook, I have to take this call.
- Sure.

113
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:18,320
Aw, honey!

114
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,200
Good job!

115
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:45,200
One, two, three!

116
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,720
It didn't do it.

117
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:50,360
You both did great today.

118
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:51,840
I'm so proud of you two.

119
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,000
Hey, Pun.

120
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,200
You did great.

121
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:01,160
How about we take them for pizza?

122
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,720
- Kongkwan, Poonpun, let's go play.
- Kongkwan, Poonpun.

123
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:05,880
Let's go.

124
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:09,800
Poonpun did great on the show, Mr. Pat.

125
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:13,440
- Yeah.
- His mom didn't come though, right?

126
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:18,200
But Kongkwan's mommy
sure is taking good care of him.

127
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,680
People might even
mistake you for his real mom.

128
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:23,400
If I didn't know you,

129
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,760
I would've thought
you three were a family.

130
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:30,840
Isn't it normal, though?

131
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,440
My kid's friends are like my kids too.

132
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,800
Or do you two not see it that way?

133
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:40,120
Do you only care about your own kids?

134
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,760
'Cause if that's the case,

135
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:46,080
I'll have to teach Kongkwan
to choose her friends wisely.

136
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:49,040
Mrs. Oh,

137
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:52,400
you might want to keep
a close eye on Satang.

138
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:54,720
The other day, Kongkwan told me

139
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,920
that Satang was crying

140
00:10:57,520 --> 00:11:00,040
because she saw her parents fighting.

141
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:04,520
So why don't you stop obsessing
over other people's business

142
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:07,680
and focus on your own family?

143
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,000
Let's talk more later.

144
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:14,680
I just remembered we have somewhere to be.

145
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:16,800
If you'll excuse us.

146
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,600
If you'll excuse us.

147
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:20,560
Let's go.

148
00:11:26,080 --> 00:11:28,160
Kongkwan, Poonpun, let's grab some pizza.

149
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,160
- Let's go, Pun.
- Yay!

150
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,480
Say goodbye.

151
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:31,760
- Bye-bye!
- Bye-bye!

152
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:32,720
See you soon, dear.

153
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:34,160
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

154
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,240
Bye-bye.

155
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:40,280
Aren't we getting pizza, Dad?

156
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,120
I'll take you some other day.

157
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,400
Today's your mommy's turn.

158
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:47,680
Why don't you two live together?

159
00:11:47,760 --> 00:11:50,080
That way, you won't have to take turns.

160
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:59,400
Poonpun doesn't get to eat pizza with us.

161
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:03,200
It's alright.

162
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:06,760
Let's invite him some other day, yeah?

163
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:08,880
- Mommy.
- Yes?

164
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:11,520
Why do grown-ups have to break up?

165
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:17,720
<i>Didn't I tell you not to be late?</i>

166
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:20,680
I had to cancel my event
at the association just to wait for you.

167
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:23,280
Mother, I want to eat pizza.

168
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,640
No.

169
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:26,880
I can't let you eat junk food.

170
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:29,440
Nam, take him to eat.

171
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:37,200
Goodbye, Father. See you on Sunday.

172
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,240
Yes.

173
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:45,720
I'll see you on Sunday.

174
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,240
- Okay.
- Okay.

175
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,560
He's still a kid, you know.

176
00:12:58,640 --> 00:13:00,080
Don't be so strict.

177
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,720
Let him do what he wants for a change.

178
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:07,080
So that he'll grow up
to be lousy like you?

179
00:13:08,400 --> 00:13:09,640
I can't have that.

180
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:13,000
My son has to become successful,
like his grandpa.

181
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:15,440
Since you're no good,
I'll just teach him myself.

182
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:17,400
No one wants to be your puppet, Prao.

183
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:21,280
And you wanting me
to be a dynastic politician,

184
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,640
I don't want that life,

185
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,920
living through your dad's connections.

186
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,160
Well, suit yourself.

187
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,920
Go ahead and run
your stupid little travel agency,

188
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,400
but don't bring our son near that…

189
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,920
oh-so-perfect manager of yours,

190
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:40,080
who's just so good at everything.

191
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,080
Just be careful.

192
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,520
You might be working at a desk now,

193
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,120
but soon you'll end up in her bed.

194
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,400
Learn to respect others for once, Prao.

195
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:50,360
You and your dad
aren't the only ones who deserve it.

196
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,880
You must be so tired from school.

197
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:15,920
Are you hungry?

198
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,720
I already ate pizza with Mommy.

199
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,400
Aw, man.

200
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:24,040
Who will eat my <i>palo</i> then?

201
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:27,080
<i>Palo</i>'s my favorite. I wanna eat some.

202
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:31,320
Just let me know
when you're hungry, alright?

203
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,720
Yes, Grandma.

204
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,240
What about you?

205
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:38,400
Probably have to be somewhere
like always, huh?

206
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:41,000
Aw, Mom. I have an appointment today.

207
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,960
Then I'll eat some for you.

208
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:44,400
Drive safe, Mom.

209
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:46,240
Aw, come here.

210
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:51,160
Aren't you just the sweetest?

211
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:53,440
Come on, honey. Go shower and get changed.

212
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:54,920
Come on.

213
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:03,600
Kongkwan's almost old enough to know.

214
00:15:03,680 --> 00:15:05,840
Do you have answers for her yet?

215
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:08,880
Have you been talking to Kuk at all?

216
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:14,160
There's nothing left to talk about, Mom.

217
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:17,080
He does his job, I do mine. That's all.

218
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:44,920
Mook.

219
00:15:45,680 --> 00:15:47,080
Is our food here?

220
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,720
<i>Hello, Mook.</i>

221
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:25,240
<i>Where are you? Everyone's here already.</i>

222
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:28,200
I'm here. I'm heading in now.

223
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:29,480
Okay!

224
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:34,400
SUNDAY 11 DECEMBER

225
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,680
Guys, cheers!

226
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:01,280
- Yeah!
- Sure.

227
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:03,360
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

228
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:06,480
- There.
- Come on.

229
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,680
Hey, hold up, Mook!

230
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:13,280
That's pure water! Isn't that cheating?

231
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:16,040
I'm the designated driver here.

232
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:18,079
Who will take us home if we're all drunk?

233
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:23,920
<i>Before--</i>

234
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:28,560
You know, I really appreciate you guys

235
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:32,040
for your hard work this past quarter.

236
00:17:32,560 --> 00:17:35,240
Even though we aren't
making enough profits,

237
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:37,520
I promise you guys

238
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:40,040
we'll get through this together.

239
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,040
Yay!

240
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,360
- Yay!
- Hell yeah!

241
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:43,640
- We fight!
- Whoo!

242
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:44,840
- Let's go!
- Come here!

243
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:46,160
We got this!

244
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,080
We got this!

245
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:49,520
- We got this!
- We got this!

246
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:52,280
- We got this!
- We got this!

247
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,360
Oh no, May!

248
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:00,800
Whan,

249
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:02,480
what's up with May?

250
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:07,160
She got dumped, and she's super sad.

251
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:10,360
Aw, come on…

252
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:13,240
It's just a guy. Why are you so sad?

253
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:15,480
Where did I go wrong?

254
00:18:15,560 --> 00:18:18,080
I treated him like a king.

255
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:21,080
I treated him better
than I treat my parents.

256
00:18:23,720 --> 00:18:25,840
I may be a bad daughter,

257
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:29,720
but I'm the best freaking girlfriend
in the world!

258
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:35,720
And yet…

259
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:40,200
he still cheated on me!

260
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:48,640
It's fine, Whan. Just let her vent.

261
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:50,920
That way, she'll feel better.

262
00:18:57,080 --> 00:19:00,240
He doesn't even feel guilty.

263
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:02,440
And he even blamed me,

264
00:19:02,520 --> 00:19:04,720
saying I'm not good enough.

265
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,480
It hurts!

266
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:11,360
Hey, May! Quit it already.

267
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:14,040
Mook's barely healed.

268
